						<summary>

						<p>Fragmentary slab lying in the Vīrabhadra temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Pārthiva, Vaiśākha śu. 15, Monday.</hi></p>						

						<p>Seems to records the installation of the deities Brahma, Vishṇu, Mahēśvara and Gurakka (village deity) by some chief (name lost) for the merit of his father Bommarāju and his mother (name lost). In characters of about the 17th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
